MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: fd841a9b37cf64657a5ec72f52363ee1, type: 3}
  m_Name: VoxelizationSettings
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembler.Voxelization.Editor::Assembler.Voxelization.Editor.VoxelizationSettings
  ManifestModel: sonnet
  PlanningModel: sonnet
  AuthoringModel: sonnet
  StyleGuidance: 'Prefer fewer parts per asset where possible.

    Prefer simplicity
    over complex details.

    A wheel should always be created using a cylinder
    primitive.

    When generating eyes make them black and 1x2x1 and put them on
    the side of the head for silliness.

    Try to limit the colours per asset to
    5 if possible.

    Prefer a boxy asset design.

    Glass parts should be a
    light blue.

    Don''t use a rounded cube primitive if any of its sides are
    <=3.

    When considering scaling assume 1 voxel is about 10cm cubed.

    Organic
    structures should de-prioritise symmetry.'
  DeterministicBrief: 1
  ExtractSemanticBriefFields: 0
  MaxPartAttempts: 3
  MaxValidationRounds: 2
  MaxReviewRounds: 1
  PartVoxelBudget: 4000
  SilhouetteIouThreshold: 0.75
  SilhouetteCoverageThreshold: 0.8
